2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a highly discriminating learning methodology to fine-tune the pre-trained DenseNet architecture, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a deep learning approach to classify skin lesions, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the classification of images of skin lesions, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper uses a Center Loss function to improve the discriminative power of the CNN, which can be seen as a technique for information retrieval.
